name: Creative Sanctuary
description: We live in a large Victorian house on a quiet street, nestled between the Mission district and Noe Valley. We're one block from the streetcar stop and five blocks from the subway. We have two bedrooms which have double beds and windows which cast their light upon the warm colored walls and ceilings of this haven. We have lots of spaces in the house where you can relax, read, listen to music and just cozy up. The kitchen is well stocked and we have a bountiful garden and back deck.
neighborhood_overview: I love how our neighborhood feels quiet but is so close to lots of hustle and bustle. There is the train nearby that takes you straight downtown and we are smack in the middle of Noe Valley (quiet and family oriented), The Mission (hip and lots of great restaurants and bars) and Bernal Heights (more good restaurants!).
host_about:
Philip: English transplant to the Bay Area and half Spanish adoptive son of hardworking Yorkshire folk. I'm married to the one, engaged to my work and in love with exploring the merging of design art and craft.

Tania: SF raised with a NY energy and an Armenian background that I am proud of. I'm an international journalist, interviewing artists and producing for radio and print. I speak several languages and love to meet people. Found my husband in a cafe in NY and came back to SF to live near my Grandma. Oh, and I love plants.

name: Classic Nob Hill Studio - Roof Deck
description:
A cute studio with nice street views and lots of light and easy access to a shared roof deck with awesome Golden Gate views.

Great, classic "Old Frisco" neighborhood.

New double-pane windows help keep out the sounds of the city.
neighborhood_overview:
Very centrally located.

Fishermans Wharf, Chinatown, North Beach, downtown, Union Square shopping, Polk Street action, are all within walking distant.

For those who prefer to ride, public transport, including the classic cable car lines, are conveniently close.

Nob Hill is Old San Francisco, filled with the cable cars and classic Victorian architecture the city is famous for.

It's also a rich neighborhood with luxury buildings and nice restaurants and expansive views of the bay and beyond. There are a Trader Joes and a Whole Foods within walking distance, not to mention a cute gourmet market on the corner one block up.

For the party-minded, Polk Street and its remarkable night life are just three blocks away.
host_about:
I'm a writer, and encourage visiting writers and editors to use this studio. This is a historic building on Nob Hill, convenient to everything. Dashiell Hammett lived in this building and, we are told, finished The Maltese Falcon here. We bought this studio to house our son while he was in college; now we rent it to tourists and visiting professionals.

We are very interested in swapping housing also.

name: Loft-like Apt./Garden
description: Located on 26th St. in wonderful Noe Valley, this beautifully large furnished open apartment (540 square feet) with separate street level entrance in a two unit building. We live in the upstairs unit. Four windows open onto the quiet rear of the house and a private entrance to a private beautifully landscaped garden.
neighborhood_overview: We love Noe Valley. It is a wonderful friendly upscale neighborhood. There is a terrific mix of people who live here, many commute to Silicon Valley via (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) busses that stop a few blocks away from our home. There are lots of charming stores and restaurants within walking distance and our location makes it easily accessible to all parts of San Francisco by public transportation. Noe Valley also has more dogs (pets) than any other part of San Francisco.
host_about: Arlene is originally from New York and grew up in the Bronx, and Leon is a third generation San Franciscan. We are both retired. Leon loves to ski and play tennis.  Arlene is involved in local community services (Neighborhood Community Court and San Francisco's Civil Grand Jury).We love to travel and have visited many interesting cultures and countries (i.e. China, India, Vietnam). We enjoy trying new restaurants and taking part in the culture that SF has to offer. We are outgoing and friendly, but respect our guests privacy. We love meeting new people from all over the world, and that is what makes our hosting so much fun.

description: Welcome to the Lower Haight! My neighborhood and the surrounding areas are filled with cafes, restaurants, bars, shops, and salons. cafes, art galleries and salons of the Lower Haight. It is walking distance to beautiful Alamo Square Park (home of the fabled
"Painted Ladies" Victorian homes), Hayes Valley, Castro, Mission, NOPA, the Panhandle, Golden Gate Park, Upper Haight, and Civic
Center.
host_about: I enjoy art, architecture, photography, hiking, traveling. I love sharing San Francisco with visitors, and I hope you feel right at home while you’re here.

name: NEST of Potrero Hill - Quiet, Stylish & Convenient
description: Comfortable, quiet private guest room, with own private bath, in well-appointed, sunny and stylish, modern townhouse. Convenient for business and vacation travelers. Atop one of the famous San Francisco hills, in the very desirable Potrero Hill neighborhood. Near to terrific restaurants, shops. Great views! Sunniest weather! Easy close-by public transportation & free street parking.
neighborhood_overview:
Staying on Potrero Hill feels like being in the country, yet in the middle of a city. Greenery and sunshine abound, while first-class restaurants, views, shops, and boutiques are all close by. Plus, its central location makes it easy to reach other parts of town, or commute down the Peninsula to Silicon Valley.

Potrero Hill is the sunniest part of San Francisco, and feels like a village within the City, with lots of trees, gardens and wonderful views in all directions.
host_about: Mature but young at heart (and fully vaccinated). Interested in the arts, music, good food, the outdoors, and all that Northern California has to offer. Longtime resident and very knowledgeable about where to go, what to see & do in and around San Francisco Bay Area.

name: San Francisco's Luxury Oasis Private Room On Noe
description:
Come enjoy a wonderful experience with a native San Franciscan and his Spanish speaking Cuban husband. Alfredo is the cook, I take out the garbage! Our mission is to make sure our home is your home while you are visiting our city by the bay.

Located on a quiet one way street in Glen Park bordering Upper Noe Valley, 2 great walkable neighborhoods with easy access to BART and MUNI, 20 minutes from SFO.

Come to our Oasis on Noe! It will be our pleasure to welcome you!
neighborhood_overview: Where Noe Valley meets Glen Park you will experience two vital neighborhoods. Great restaurants nearby that we can recommend and MUNI,   San Francisco’s main transportation is just a couple of minutes away to get you to the financial district or South of Market.  The lively Mission district is close by, as well as the Castro District or Bernal Heights. The airport is 20 minutes away by UBER or LYFT.
host_about: My husband and very proud Cubano Alfredo and I have lived together in our home since 1986. We met in NYC in the 80's when we both lived there. We returned to my San Francisco roots as I am a 4th generation San Franciscan who was ready to come home to my city by the bay! Alfredo tends to the garden, I do the flowers in the house! description: 1890 renovated Victorian,  an authentic San Francisco experience. Centrally located 3 bdms,  2 ba, fully equipped kitchen, laundry, cozy backyard w dining & new BBQ grill. Gorgeous views of downtown from front terrace. Walk to Haight-Ashbury, Golden Gate Park, the Castro, Alamo Square (Painted Ladies), Hayes Valley.  Walk to grocery, cafes & restaurants. Great urban hiking from house. Buses and subway within 2 blocks.  Free parking at the house, see full description for details.
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is simply beautiful, with restored late 1800/early 1900's Victorians all around.  Buena Vista Park is just a couple of blocks up the hill surrounded by amazing archictectural gems and breathtaking views of the city and the bay.  Duboce Park a block away is also surrounded by such quaint beautiful houses that they are on the tour bus route (those buses avoid our block because of our short  hill, keeping this section of our street a quiet secret!)  Yet with Haight St and Divisadero just a block away, public transportation, grocery stores, cafes and restaurants abound within a short walk.
host_about:
I came to San Francisco for the first time many years ago to visit my daughter.  I couldn't visit for long, sleeping in her and her roommate's living room. Time together was precious, hotels were too far and too expensive.  My dream of owning a house close to daughter and grandchildren came true.
  I am now  living the dream of hosting fellow visiting parents and grandparents, in addition to vacationers, business travelers,  individuals and families the world over.  I really enjoy sharing my house and my city.
My husband and I love family, friends, music, nature, great food and wine, old movies, sports.  We are hikers, birders and world travelers.  We appreciate cultural diversity and individual uniqueness.
My motto:  Dream it, love it, expect it, and you will experience it!

name: Calm & Cool, Safe & Sunny on Bernal Hill
description: Enjoy a quiet getaway in picturesque Bernal Heights - one of San Francisco's safest and sunniest neighborhoods.
neighborhood_overview:
Here in Bernal Heights, the vibrant buzz of Mission Street gives way to the stylish calm of Cortland Avenue. With numerous specialty shops, boutiques, and galleries just steps away, and more than thirty cafes and restaurants within easy walking distance, Bernal Heights is an eclectic shopping and foodie destination.

Be sure to check out the fresh produce, flowers, and specialty foods at the Farmer's Market every Saturday morning and an amazing assortment of antiques, collectibles, jewelry, art, and other one-of-a-kind treasures at the iconic open-air Alemany Flea Market every Sunday morning.

For a bird's-eye view of San Francisco and beyond, join neighborhood dog-walkers, families, and the occasional jogger, and enjoy a leisurely stroll to the top of Bernal Heights Park, just a few minutes up the hill from Cortland Avenue. Take in the 360-degree vista at the summit and stay for an unforgettable sunset (bring an extra layer as the cooler ocean breeze tends to pic
host_about:
I'm a third-generation native Californian born in Oakland and raised all over the Bay Area. As a single, gay man, my heart and home have been anchored in San Francisco since 2002, and there is nowhere else I'd rather be. 

Travel and relocation have been prominent features of my life from an early age. I've lived in the Midwest and East Coast in the US as well as in Latin America, Western and Eastern Europe, and Central Asia. I was a university student in Spain, a Peace Corps volunteer in Paraguay, and a humanitarian aid worker in Bosnia, Serbia, Tajikistan, and Afghanistan. 

I'm also an antiques dealer - for vintage, salvage, and upcycled furniture, decor, and jewelry. My home features many objects & artifacts I've collected or repurposed over the years. One of my favorite pastimes is poking around sidewalk sales and thrift stores... but some of my treasures were just as likely found 'free online' or on the street corner. 

I'd love for you to come check out my place! Thanks for reading this far and I look forward to meeting you soon.

name: Best Views in all of San Francisco
description: The perfect place to enjoy VIEWS atop Noe Valley, the most central location within San Francisco. This 2nd story walk-up unit has hardwood floors, recessed lights w/ dimmers, large empty closets, and luxury bathrooms. Free HD Cable with DVR and HBO. Free high speed wifi. Huge sunny patio w/ hammock, sun lounger and zen rock garden. [DISCLAIMER: In extenuating circumstances, you may be asked to move to a newly renovated 3rd story unit w/ same interior floor plan.]
neighborhood_overview:
If you are interested in exploring the neighborhood around the Vista Point, it's a short 10 minute walk down the hill to the many shops and restaurants located along 24th Street in the heart of Noe Valley all the way to the hip and trendy Mission district.

Just up the hill, Twin Peaks is a breath-taking neighborhood that rises above the rest (literally!). Occupying two of San Francisco’s highest summits, Twin Peaks offers quiet seclusion from the city below. The neighborhood’s high altitude location may remove it from hurried urban activity, but the steep descent from its hilltops is made worth it by Twin Peaks’ sweeping San Francisco vistas.

name: Family-Friendly Flat In San Francisco, CA. USA
description: Despite what you've heard or read, San Francisco remains an amazing town, that's once again reinventing itself.  A.I.'s  here so thank you for joining us for the next chapter.
neighborhood_overview:
GLEN PARK is really like a little village in the very center of the city. There are a variety of really good restaurants, from our authentic French bistro, Le P'tit Laurent, American fare at Chenery Park, Gialina Pizzeria, La Corneta Taqueria, Eco Sushi, and Osha Thai restaurant.

For breakfast, try Destination Bakery for fresh brioche, Tyger's Coffee Shop, or my favorite, Higher Grounds, where they serve amazing crepes.

The village has a great independent bookstore, the Bird & Beckett, and there’s live jazz on Friday and Sunday nights.

There’s a terrific gourmet supermarket, Canyon Market (see photos). Finally, the Village has its very own Farmer's Market on Sundays, selling local produce from farms all over the Bay Area. Yummmm!

GLEN CANYON PARK: Just one block from the flat is Glen Canyon Park. Unlike any other park in the City, it is situated in a rustic canyon, with 70 bucolic acres . There are easy walking trails along Islais C
host_about:
The story of who I am, and how I came to live in this most beautiful city, can be found in my recent book of poetry, "When You Run Out of America You've Arrived in San Francisco."  It's available on Amazon.

For the past 12 seasons, I've been an Airbnb host here a Maison Swiss, and it’s been a wonderful experience meeting folks from all over the world.  

My hundreds of five star reviews say it all

name: Forest Garden Suite Near UCSF
description:
*Minimum 30-day rental

Hello! Our suite has recently been refurbished with a bathroom remodel, fresh paint, new TV and many other upgrades. We've organized it to be private, secure and comfortable. We aim to create an atmosphere that is enjoyable and restful.
neighborhood_overview:
Our fully-contained suite is located in the thriving Inner Sunset district, a safe residential neighborhood and one of San Francisco's most vibrant communities. Our Walk Score is 94 out of 100, a "Walkers Paradise" meaning daily activities do not require a car. There are many options for dining and just about every type of world cuisine is found in the excellent neighborhood restaurants--this is not an exaggeration. Please take a moment to look at our recommendations in our Host Guidebook which features our favorite places.

In addition to dining options, the area is brimming with cafes, sports bars, retail shops, a post office, hardware store, drug store, laundromats, bakeries, a grocery market, and banks all within a five minute walk from the suite. There's a bustling Farmer's Market with organic produce and fresh artisan goods every Sunday.

The suite is an 8-minute walk to the University of California (UCSF) campus and medical center, convenient for anyone asso
host_about:
We're proud of our excellent ratings, so please take a moment to read our reviews! We strive to make your stay with us a five-star experience.

We have lived in our home for over 25 years and every day we feel fortunate that we live in beautiful San Francisco.  Our children were raised in our great neighborhood, the Inner Sunset district, and many of our neighbors are longtime friends. We're excited to share the wonders of the city to all who visit our SF Suite.

Both of us are career media professionals who have joyfully  transitioned to working in community arts organizations.  

We have visited many places in the U.S. and abroad  and our many travel experiences have given us great insight in how to host. We have always enjoyed staying in private spaces to get a feel for how the locals live. On our travels we have enjoyed cooking our own meals as well as eating out. Hopefully our guests will benefit from what we've learned along the way about hospitality and comfort. 

Our hosting style is service-oriented but not intrusive, where your privacy and comfort is our priority. We live on the premises, above the suite and are always available to help our guests have the best stay possible.  We look forward to meeting you!

~Syl and Art

name: Elegant Victorian Flat in Haight
description:
This is an elegant victorian home WITH A LOT OF TAXIDERMY, beautiful antiques and art. A classic bit of Americana...

There is also some erotic art in my bedroom. So if this offends you then my place isn't for you.

Please look at ALL the photos before you book :)
neighborhood_overview:
Haight Ashbury is a famous tourist attraction because it was a center for the hippies of the 1960s. now there are many cool bars and good shopping for hip clothes and shoes in addition to cool vintage clothing. My favorite restaurant is Zazie at 941 Cole Street with excellent brunch on weekends and lunch on weekdays. Both places are only a five-minute walk.
There is a Whole Foods supermarket one block away at the end of Haight Street. There is a better market on Haight Street between Clayton and Ashbury Streets called Gus's Ashbury Market. It is five blocks from my house.
There are three pizza restaurants on Haight Street. The best one is Bizza on Haight Street near Masonic Street.

name: Twin Peaks Home Available for 3+ Month Stays
description:
Our home is located in a quiet, safe neighborhood on the western slope of Twin Peaks. The two upstairs bedrooms are available for rent, on the same floor as the shared kitchen, living & dining rooms and full bath.

We reserve the downstairs bedroom and half bath for ourselves. We spend the majority of the year traveling and working from the road, so chances are that you will have the house to yourself for the majority of your stay.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is quiet and safe and in the geographic center of the city. It's paradise for those who like to walk or run hills.

The walk up to the city's highest point (Twin Peaks) and its 360 degree views takes just 10 minutes. There are numerous hilltop parks and forested trails. Check the book "Stairway Walks in San Francisco". There are many artful stairway walks throughout the city that originate near our house. Cafe's and restaurants are a 20-30 minute walk away in any direction.
host_about:
I and my partner Ellen are home owners in the vibrant city of San Francisco. We are travelers by nature, leaning toward the outdoors: camping, hiking & backpacking, while remaining immersed in the social and culturally rich world of the city.

We're into cooking, music, biking, long walks and hosting gatherings with our friends.

Life is Grand!

name: Private Room w/ 2 Queen Beds, Steps to Ocean Beach
description:
Comfortable Queen Size Bed in Shared Bedroom. Across street from Ocean Beach and 5 blocks to Golden Gate Park. 3 blocks to the N line train. 1 block to the #7 bus.

Our beautiful neighborhood gives you easy access to both nature and city.

Nice kitchen, granite counter tops, stainless steel appliances, hardwood floors, free laundry, 45mbs internet.

Our home is comfortable and convenient.

Calendar is open for January, but we are open to longer term renters as well.
neighborhood_overview: This neighborhood is San Francisco's best kept secret.  Quiet, but within a quick commute to all of the hustle and bustle of downtown, Ocean Beach revolves around two main places -- 5 miles of beach fronting the Pacific Ocean and Golden Gate Park, one of the best urban parks in the country.
host_about: I am a political theorist, a privacy advocate, a big wave surfer and an innovation coach.  You can learn more about both my work and my play by looking for my blog online.  Airbnb doesn't allow you to list websites but you can search for it: my name is Matthew Schutte. And my blog is: "Matthew Schutte  |  on the future of the internet and society, with a dash of surfing and play"

name: Sunny Potrero Townhouse "Nest"
description: Two comfortable, quiet guest rooms and two private baths in well-appointed and stylish townhouse. On top of one of the famous SF Hills, in the desirable Potrero Hill neighborhood. Great views! Easy transportation & street parking.
neighborhood_overview: Potrero Hill has the best weather and views in San Francisco. I like the feeling of being a bit in the country (many trees, birds), but also really being in the City. There are excellent restaurants nearby (mostly on 18th Street, or at the foot of the hill in the "Dogpatch" neighborhood), as well as some lovely unique small shops.
host_about: Mature but young at heart (and fully vaccinated). Interested in the arts, music, good food, the outdoors, and all that Northern California has to offer. Longtime resident and very knowledgeable about where to go, what to see & do in and around San Francisco Bay Area.

name: Clean Suite with private bath near Ocean Beach
description: Your own private space on the first level of a house - clean, newly remodeled, furnished in an interesting neighborhood with lots of restaurants and easy access to downtown.
neighborhood_overview: We have a great neighborhood!  Literally around the corner is a grocery store, burrito joint, very popular bakery, pub, burger joint, Chinese food restaurant, Korean bar/restaurant, cafe and more.
host_about:
We've lived near Ocean Beach for 30 years.  We enjoy our neighborhood... Bill is a surfer and will even fish off the beach.  I (Ashli) tend to work a great deal, but I enjoy that!  I'm an event producer.

We both have traveled a great deal and enjoy meeting people from all over.  Over the years, we've had people from all over the world live in our studio downstairs.  Bill is fluent in Spanish (Ashli's Spanish is passable - barely).

name: Stay in a historic apt in the heart of the Mission
description: You'll love staying in our three bedroom, two bath apartment located on the top floor of a 1902 Edwardian building. It's private and all yours. In the heart of the Mission District with murals, shops, cafes, restaurants, and bars -- all within easy walking distance. And a 5 minute walk from the 24th BART station!
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is on Shotwell St next to 24th St corridor (and very close to Mission and Valencia streets) with lots of shops, coffee shops, restaurants, bars and the famous Balmy Alley murals. Easy walking distance to everything you need - grocery stores, several parks, and Bernal Hill for amazing views of San Francisco. 5 minute walk to 24th St BART Station which is a  couple of blocks away.
host_about: Our San Francisco airbnb listing is 279184.

name: North Beach Best Location and View
description: Views - Views- Views of San Francisco's downtown Skyline and unobstructed view of the Pyramid Building located in the heart of North Beach touristy neighborhood in San Francisco. My Apt is one bedroom with a king-sized pillow top bed and a full-sized sofa bed in the living room.
neighborhood_overview: A variety of trendy watering holes, wonderful restaurants and site seeing  attractions.   a galore of entertainment, comedy and live theater.  Authentic Italian restaurants and coffee cafes.  City Lights Books and Chinatown is a half block from my place.  With a WalkScore of 100; you can walk to at least 7 of the top 10 attractions in the City.  Fisherman's Wharf, Pier 39 and The Exploratorium is located at the foot of Broadway Street on the waterfront.  Three blocks from Coit Tower.   Walk to the Crookedest Street in the world on Lombard Street off Columbus Ave.   Washington Square Park, The Ferry Building and Embarcadero Shopping Center are in my neighborhood.   A 10 minute walk through Chinatown will land you steps from Maiden Lane and Union Square where you'll find all the famous High end designer boutiques like Gucci, Prada, Dolce & Gabbana...and more.  There's so many wonderful things to see, do and tour in my neighborhood.  Last we have several excellent bakeries; Brioche's and
host_about: Native of California.   I love to travel.  I've been around  the world; spenting time in  South east Asia,  Japan,  Hong  Kong and Thailand.  Worked  in Sydney Australia for a short while.  Spent several months in Milan Italy where I have a cousin.  Visited many parts of Europe including Germany, France, Greece and  England...  I enjoy meeting new people and understanding other cultures and their way of life.  I do a lot of walking, Iyengar yoga, playing golf, watching sports and live comedy.  Above all, I'm a  seeker of great  food  and  spirits
